headline: General Electric (GE): Reviewing GE’s Valuation After Raised Outlook and Strong Q3 Earnings Results
summary: General Electric (GE) posted third-quarter results that came in ahead of expectations, prompting the company to boost its full-year outlook for revenue, profit, and earnings. Investor attention has focused on management’s upbeat tone and the positive momentum in key business segments. See our latest analysis for General Electric. The raised outlook and standout third-quarter numbers have clearly caught investors’ attention, fueling a remarkable 80% year-to-date share price return for General...
